    {
      "id": "l9-words",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Polite words",
      "body": "# Polite words\n\nA few words smooth almost every interaction:\n\n- **Sorry** (माफ़ कीजिए) — to apologise\n- **You are welcome.** (आपका स्वागत है।) — reply to *thank you*\n- **Of course.** (ज़रूर।) and **No problem.** (कोई बात नहीं।)\n- **May I?** (क्या मैं कर सकता हूँ?) — to ask permission\n\nEnglish does not change verbs for respect (आप vs तुम). Politeness comes from these **extra words** — *sorry*, *please*, *thank you* — not from the verb form."
    },
